title: Grateful Dead Live at Providence Civic Center on 1983-04-20
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) > Korg MR-1000 (1-bit/5.6MHz) > Audiogate (1-bit/5.6MHz > 16-bit/44.1KHz) > cdwav (edits)
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Gray-> Promised Land, Loser, Minglewood Blues, Ramble On Rose, Me & My Uncle-> Cumberland Blues, Looks Like Rain, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

My Brother Esau-> Maybe You Know, Bertha-> Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Throwing Stones-> Morning Dew-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text:
Overshadowed by some of the monster other shows on this tour but fun to go to anyway..... Spotty at times but I was there and while this is never going to be on anyone's top 50, there is some great stuff on here all the same particularly the China>Rider which is ripping. Cumberland and Estimated>Eyes, & Throwing Stones>A+ Dew> Sugar Mag gets a nod as well.

As setlists and stories started pouring in from UVM, Byrne, Broome, expecations were very high here and in New Haven which would have been tough to achieve.

I don't recall them ever playing a bad show here. This is worth a listen to as no show was ever 100pct.  

All of that said listening to this Morning Dew after all of this time, this is a hot one. You have to remember at this time, this was played pretty rarely and in my judgement may be hotter than UVM.
